the lived experiences of our vitality. In an age marked by increasing anxiety about the homogenizing tendencies of contemporary life, In Vivo is timely and revelatory. Informed by a range of philosophical thinking and examples from art, music, and literature, it illustrates opportunities for meaningful reflection that are available to everyone, and urges the reader to engage with them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aLife change events. 0aLife. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355772740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773557727423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773557727/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles